<p>I need to logging all save/delete methods in JPARepository. I need to save in logs who did it, what method (save or delete) and when dit it.</p>  <p>Yes, I can put manually in each method save/delete of JPARepository methods of logService. But maybe anybody know another way how to do it automatically (maybe using annotations).</p>  <p><strong>UPDATED:</strong> I'm trying to write logs using aspects.  I've added to my WebConfig:</p>  <pre><code>@EnableAspectJAutoProxy public class WebConfig extends WebMvcConfigurerAdapter { </code></pre>  <p>and created LogAspect:</p>  <pre><code>@Aspect public class LogAspect {      @Before("com.springapp.mvc.repositories")     public void writeLog(){         System.out.println("write log");     }  } </code></pre>  <p>Added dependency:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;dependency&gt;             &lt;groupId&gt;aspectj&lt;/groupId&gt;             &lt;artifactId&gt;aspectjweaver&lt;/artifactId&gt;             &lt;version&gt;1.5.4&lt;/version&gt;         &lt;/dependency&gt; </code></pre>  <p>but when I call repository methods, message "write log" not appears in console.</p>  <p><strong>UPDATED</strong></p>  <p>Ok, I solved my problems by several steps:</p>  <ol> <li>Upgraded spring to version <code>4.2.1.RELEASE</code></li> <li>Added <code>@Component</code> to <code>LogAspect</code></li> <li>Changed <code>@EnableAspectJAutoProxy</code> to <code>@EnableAspectJAutoProxy(proxyTargetClass = true)</code></li> <li>Changed <code>@Before("execution(* com.springapp.mvc.repositories.*.*(*)))")</code></li> </ol>  <p><strong>LAST QUESTION:</strong> in my logs I need to know which repository (UserRepository, ImageRepository or else) was called and which method (save or delete). First * after com.springapp.mvc.repositories is which repository was called, and second which method.  Is it possible to retrive it inside method?</p>